      "writtenOn": "2019-08-29T18:26:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "With Breakpad, the client_id was the same as the UMA client_id (using this Crashpad owned client_id instead of the UMA client_id is preferred for privacy). I\u0027m pretty sure this value was unique per-device and not per-account (it was the value in \"/home/chronos/Consent To Send Stats\"). I agree that we can\u0027t store reports in this database because that data needs to be kept in each users sub file system, but I think using it for device-wide settings is consistent with Breakpad\u0027s behavior.\n\nI\u0027ll let this keep writing reports for now, and leave it up to crash_reporter/crash_sender to figure consent.",
